  224              
  225              /CONSTANTS
  226              / THE VALUE FOR BDTIME IS THE TWOS COMPLEMENT OF THE NUMBER OF COUNTS
  227              / OF THE TIMING LOOP FOR A SINGLE CHARACTER TRANSMISSION.  IT SHOULD
  228              / BE TUNED FOR YOUR MACHINE.  HERE ARE SOME EXAMPLES FOR REFERENCE.
  229              /BDTIME, 7260           / PDP-8/e 4800 8N1 ON M8655 (6.2US PER LOOP)
  230              /BDTIME, 7530           / PDP-8/e 9600 8N1 ON M8655 (6.2US PER LOOP)
  231              /BDTIME, 7654           / PDP-8/e 19200 8N1 ON M8655 (6.2US PER LOOP)
  232              /BDTIME, 7726           / PDP-8/e 38400 8N1 ESTIMATE (6.2US PER LOOP)
  233              /BDTIME, 7746           / SIMH AT DEFAULT SETTINGS (OVER 62K BAUD?)
  234              /BDTIME, 7762           / PDP-8/e 115200 8N1 ESTIMATE (6.2US PER LOOP)
  235              /BDTIME, 7771           / PDP-8/e 230400 8N1 ESTIMATE (6.2US PER LOOP)
  236              / THE CONSTANT WAS MOVED INTO THE LOOP TO FILL AN ALWAYS SKIPPED SPACE
  237              
  238              / COMMAND TO WAKEUP THE SERVER.  MUST BE AN UNUSED CONTROL CHARACTER.
  239              / A TELETYPE SENDS THE 0200 BIT SET SO WE SHOULD BE ABLE TO USE ANY
  240              / VALUES BELOW 0200.  LETS AVOID THE COMMON ONES ANYWAY.
  241              / 000  NUL      FEED HOLES OR CR-LF TIMING
  242              / 007  BEL      RING THE BELL
  243              / 010  BS       BACKSPACE
  244              / 011  HT       TAB
  245              / 012  LF       LINEFEED
  246              / 013  VT       VERTICAL TAB
  247              / 014  FF       FORM FEED
  248              / 015  CR       CARRIAGE RETURN
  249              / 033  ESC      ESCAPE
  250              / 040  SPACE    SPACE
  251              / 0177 DEL      DELETE
  252              /WE NEED A RANGE OF 8.  THE BOTTOM 3 BITS ARE THE CALLERS DATA FIELD.
  253              /020 THROUGH 027 SEEM USABLE.
  254              
  255              /THE WKUP CONSTANT WAS MOVED TO THE FRONT IN ORDER TO PAD THE 2ND
  256              /ENTRY POINT TO THE CORRECT PLACE
  257              
  258              /PERSISTENT VARIABLES
  259 07742* 0000  TSFSET, 0               / 7777 IF TSF FLAG WAS SET UPON ENTRY
  260 07743* 0000  KSFSET, 0               / 7777 IF KSF WAS SET UPON ENTRY
  261              
  262              
  263              / PAD THE REST OF THE HANDLER SPACE WITH ZEROS.  IT IS NOT NECESSARY
  264              / BUT MAKES THE BOOT BLOCK MORE CONSISTENT.
  265                      ZBLOCK 7744-.
  266              
  267              /VARIABLES USING THE DATA BREAK ADDRESSES
  268        7750  CA=7750                 /CALLERS TRANSFER ADDRESS
  269        7751  WC=7751                 /WORDS COUNT AS TWO'S COMPLEMENT



